Elisaveta Ivanovna Bykova (or Elisabeth Bykova, Russian: Елизаве́та Ива́новна Бы́кова; November 4, 1913 in Bogolyubovo, Vladimir Oblast, Russian Empire – March 8, 1989 in [MASK], Soviet Union) was a Soviet chess player and the third and fifth Women's World Chess Champion, from 1953 until 1956, and again from 1958 to 1962.
